commit.message: Enough coding for today. Fixing stoopid mistake.
Some refactoring to fix coloring issues.
Minor tweaks to align header content of all shell files.
The `shellcheck` version on Travis CI is 0.6.3, which doesn't support the `.shellcheckrc` file yet.
Move common shellcheck options to `.shellcheckrc`, and cleanup remaining.
SC3044 == SC2039 in previous ShellCheck versions.

Fixed issue #32 -- assertEquals fails in bash when "nullglob" is set.

Cleaned up the `_SHUNIT_LINENO_` macro a bit, and added the `shunit2_shopt_test.sh` to test `nullglob` support. To be consistent in the determination of whether `shopt` works, also refactored `shunit_macros_test.sh` and `shunit2_test_helpers` by moving the `th_isLinenoWorking()` function into the test as it is only used there.
Slight wording and emphasis improvements to indicate need for double-quoting with macros.
Fixed test failure for previous submit.
Fix bug where the content wasn't output for debugging.
Fix `set -e` issues caught by mksh shell.
Fix grepping issue that was mistakenly a regexp, and also non-zero return codes.
Pipe grep output to /dev/null instead of using -q to be more portable.
Add example of testing command output.
Fix capitalization of setUp() functions and comments.

Fix issue #145 -- Allow skipping tests with a descriptive message.

An optional message can be provided when skipping is started. Assuming a message of 'Some message.', the output will look like this:

shunit2:WARN [skipping] Some message.
Prefix some stuff with ${__SHUNIT_BUILTIN}.
Added demonstration that issue #123 is no longer a problem.
Update copyright year.
Fixed issue #133.
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master'
Commit fixes for issue #14, along with some additional cleanups.
Fix function description.
Merge branch 'master' into p138
Fix incorrect test case in testAssertNotNull().
